<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=66.php.html" title="Edit section: Broadcasters">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Broadcasters">Broadcasters</span></h2>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=67.php.html" title="Edit section: Radio">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Radio">Radio</span></h3>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="Detroit_Tigers_Radio_Network" title="Detroit Tigers Radio Network">Detroit Tigers Radio Network</a></div>
<p>The Tigers' current <a href="Flagship_(radio)" title="Flagship (radio)" class="mw-redirect">flagship radio stations</a> are Detroit sister stations <a href="WXYT-AM" title="WXYT-AM" class="mw-redirect">WXYT-AM</a> (1270 AM) and <a href="WXYT-FM" title="WXYT-FM">WXYT-FM</a> (97.1 FM).<sup id="cite_ref-56" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-56"><span>[</span>56<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="Dan_Dickerson" title="Dan Dickerson">Dan Dickerson</a> does <a href="Play-by-play" title="Play-by-play" class="mw-redirect">play-by-play</a> and former Tigers catcher <a href="Jim_Price_(baseball)" title="Jim Price (baseball)">Jim Price</a> does <a href="Color_commentary" title="Color commentary" class="mw-redirect">color commentary</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-broadcasters_57-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-broadcasters-57"><span>[</span>57<span>]</span></a></sup> Games are carried on both stations unless a conflict with <a href="Detroit_Lions" title="Detroit Lions">Detroit Lions</a>, <a href="Detroit_Pistons" title="Detroit Pistons">Detroit Pistons</a> or <a href="Detroit_Red_Wings" title="Detroit Red Wings">Detroit Red Wings</a> coverage arises, in which case only WXYT-AM serves as the Tigers' flagship.</p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=68.php.html" title="Edit section: Television">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Television">Television</span></h3>
<p>The Tigers' current exclusive local television rights holder is <a href="Fox_Sports_Detroit" title="Fox Sports Detroit">Fox Sports Detroit</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-fsd_58-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-fsd-58"><span>[</span>58<span>]</span></a></sup> <a href="Mario_Impemba" title="Mario Impemba">Mario Impemba</a> does play-by-play with former outfielder <a href="Rod_Allen" title="Rod Allen">Rod Allen</a> handling color commentary.<sup id="cite_ref-broadcasters_57-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-broadcasters-57"><span>[</span>57<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=69.php.html" title="Edit section: Former">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Former">Former</span></h3>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="List_of_Detroit_Tigers_broadcasters" title="List of Detroit Tigers broadcasters">List of Detroit Tigers broadcasters</a></div>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=70.php.html" title="Edit section: Franchise records">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Franchise_records">Franchise records</span></h2>
<div class="rellink relarticle mainarticle">Main article: <a href="Detroit_Tigers_team_records" title="Detroit Tigers team records" class="mw-redirect">Detroit Tigers team records</a></div>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Detroit_Tigers&action=edit&section=71.php.html" title="Edit section: Season records">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Season_records">Season records</span></h3>
<ul>
<li>Highest Batting Average: .420, <a href="Ty_Cobb" title="Ty Cobb">Ty Cobb</a> (1911)</li>
<li>Most Runs: 147, <a href="Ty_Cobb" title="Ty Cobb">Ty Cobb</a> (1911)</li>
<li>Most Hits: 248, <a href="Ty_Cobb" title="Ty Cobb">Ty Cobb</a> (1911)</li>
<li>Highest Slugging&#160;%: .683, <a href="Hank_Greenberg" title="Hank Greenberg">Hank Greenberg</a> (1938)</li>
<li>Most Doubles: 63, <a href="Hank_Greenberg" title="Hank Greenberg">Hank Greenberg</a> (1934)</li>
<li>Most Triples: 26, <a href="Sam_Crawford" title="Sam Crawford">Sam Crawford</a> (1914)</li>
<li>Most Home Runs: 58, <a href="Hank_Greenberg" title="Hank Greenberg">Hank Greenberg</a> (1938)</li>
<li>Most Grand Slams: 4, <a href="Rudy_York" title="Rudy York">Rudy York</a> (1938), <a href="Ray_Boone" title="Ray Boone">Ray Boone</a> (1953) and <a href="Jim_Northrup_(baseball)" title="Jim Northrup (baseball)">Jim Northrup</a> (1968)</li>
<li>Most RBIs: 183, <a href="Hank_Greenberg" title="Hank Greenberg">Hank Greenberg</a> (1937)</li>
<li>Most Stolen Bases: 96, <a href="Ty_Cobb" title="Ty Cobb">Ty Cobb</a> (1915)</li>
<li>Most Wins: 31, <a href="Denny_McLain" title="Denny McLain">Denny McLain</a> (1968)</li>
<li>Lowest ERA: 1.63, <a href="Ed_Summers" title="Ed Summers">Ed Summers</a> (1908)</li>
<li>Strikeouts: 308, <a href="Mickey_Lolich" title="Mickey Lolich">Mickey Lolich</a> (1971)</li>
<li>Complete Games: 42, <a href="George_Mullin_(baseball)" title="George Mullin (baseball)">George Mullin</a> (1904)</li>
<li>Saves: 49, <a href="Jos%C3%A9_Valverde" title="José Valverde">José Valverde</a> (2011)</li>
</ul>
